      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PAW FARINA (1) doesn't have the best strike-rate but recent form is sound. Has finished in the money at the last three runs. Has never been out of the money in six starts this course. Can measure up this time. CARLEY'S IMAGE (4) is progressing well scoring last time out (25.27) at this track and bringing up her 3rd career win. Solid record at the distance winning three races. Leading chance again. BUSH BIG SHOW (3) scored well last start as odds-on favourite by 2.5 lengths at Geelong in a handy 22.68 beating Paw Maddox. Draws to advantage and has the ability and in winning form. Makes plenty of appeal on the back of that last-start win. SO YOU ASSUME (7) was beaten into fifth last time but ran impressive time with a slick 23.31. Worth thought on that run.",
